When I first began delving into reactive client interface frameworks. This was one of my biggest gripes. It looks, and reads like a giant confusing mess. I finally came across <a href="http://vuejs.org/" rel="nofollow">http://vuejs.org/</a> and I haven&#x27;t looked back. Simple binding syntax to html elements, and powerful enough for most projects without being heavyweight.<p>I mean it doesn&#x27;t get any more straightforward than this.<p><div id=&quot;app&quot;>
  <p>{{ message }}</p>
  <input v-model=&quot;message&quot;>
</div><p>new Vue({
  el: &#x27;#app&#x27;,
  data: {
    message: &#x27;Hello Vue.js!&#x27;
  }
})
